## Additional Term: Anti-996

The software may NOT be used by any entity that enforces a "996" work schedule
(9:00 AM – 9:00 PM, 6 days per week) or any similarly exploitative labor
practice as defined by the 996.ICU movement (https://996.icu).

This includes, but is not limited to:

- Any organization that requires employees to work more than 40 hours per week
  on a regular basis without overtime compensation
- Any organization that penalizes employees for refusing unpaid overtime
- Any organization classified under the 996 company list maintained by the
  996.ICU community

Where such restrictions conflict with local law, the remaining terms of this
license shall continue to apply.

The purpose of this clause is to promote fair labor practices. Individuals and
organizations that respect work-life balance are warmly welcome to use this
software.
